.:: Puzzle 2x7-Level-1-6::.
City: nizza, london, marseilles, liverpool, san-francisco, rome, berlin
The people use 7 different means of transport: bus, jet-ski, quad-bike, ship, skateboard, tram, trike
 1. the person traveling to rome is on the right of the person driving the ship##1
 2. the person traveling to nizza is the person driving the bus##1
 3. the person traveling to san-francisco is on the right of the person driving the jet-ski##1
 4. the person driving the bus is on the left of the person driving the tram##1
 5. the person driving the trike is on the right of the person traveling to berlin##1
 6. the person traveling to rome is on the left of the person traveling to nizza##1
 7. the person traveling to liverpool is in the middle##1
 8. the person traveling to marseilles is on the left of the person driving the skateboard##1
 9. the person traveling to london is on the right of the person driving the trike##1
10. the person traveling to marseilles is on the left of the person traveling to rome##1

.:: Answer ::.
|             |   1    |     2      |  3  |    4     |    5    |   6   |      7      |
| City    | marseilles | rome   | nizza | liverpool | berlin  | san-francisco | london |
| Transport   | ship   | skateboard | bus | tram     | jet-ski | trike | quad-bike   |

